	<titles>
		<title type="short" as="introduced">Common Sense Budget Act of 1993</title>
		<title type="official" as="introduced">To require the Congress and the President to use the spending levels for the current fiscal year (without adjustment for inflation) in the preparation of the budget for each new fiscal year in order to clearly identify spending increases from one fiscal year to the next fiscal year.</title>
